Can I do anything to help?

495
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,720
Should I wash the vegetables?

496
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:21,799
Sure.

497
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:23,039
Which one?

498
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:24,799
This?

499
00:26:24,799 --> 00:26:25,880
Okay.

500
00:26:26,799 --> 00:26:27,880
Hold on.

501
00:26:28,839 --> 00:26:30,759
I'll tie an apron for you.

502
00:26:30,759 --> 00:26:32,960
- Don't get your clothes dirty. - No need.

503
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,039
Here.

504
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:35,640
It's okay.

505
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,240
Don't you think the scene...

506
00:26:46,319 --> 00:26:48,039
is heartwarming?

507
00:26:48,519 --> 00:26:49,519
It's like we are...

508
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:51,799
an old married couple.

509
00:26:53,279 --> 00:26:54,599
I'll do it. Come on.

510
00:26:54,599 --> 00:26:55,599
I'm almost done.

511
00:26:55,599 --> 00:26:56,680
I'll do it myself.

512
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:57,799
You do your stuff.

513
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:04,960
I'll tie it again for you.

514
00:27:05,079 --> 00:27:07,359
What are you doing? Why tie it again?

515
00:27:07,359 --> 00:27:08,960
I got it. Don't move.

516
00:27:10,279 --> 00:27:11,319
Stop it.

517
00:27:53,599 --> 00:27:56,200
Loneliness is an illness.

518
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:51,920
(Loneliness is an illness.)

519
00:29:02,039 --> 00:29:03,440
It's an ancestral antidote...

520
00:29:04,559 --> 00:29:05,880
to treat loneliness.

521
00:29:21,599 --> 00:29:23,680
Look at this light.

522
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:25,640
This music...

523
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:27,400
really sets the mood.

524
00:29:28,039 --> 00:29:29,599
Shouldn't we have a drink?

525
00:29:30,559 --> 00:29:31,680
You can drink. Here.

526
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,119
I mean drink together. What's the point of drinking myself?

527
00:29:34,519 --> 00:29:36,680
I told you. I can't drink when I'm working.

528
00:29:37,519 --> 00:29:39,160
Today, let's not talk about work.

529
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:42,160
Let's relax today.

530
00:29:42,559 --> 00:29:44,319
To this quiet night.

531
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:46,400
Are you sure...

532
00:29:47,839 --> 00:29:49,680
that no matter what happens,

533
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,680
you won't walk out that door?

534
00:29:51,839 --> 00:29:53,799
I promise I won't leave.

535
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:56,039
If I have to leave, I'll leave through the window.

536
00:29:56,039 --> 00:29:57,079
All right?

537
00:29:57,079 --> 00:29:58,160
You'll fall to your death.

538
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:01,640
Come on.

539
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:04,160
Okay, since I'm feeling good today.

540
00:30:05,359 --> 00:30:06,359
Today,

541
00:30:07,079 --> 00:30:10,480
this drink together with all these dishes...

542
00:30:10,799 --> 00:30:13,119
are to welcome you.

543
00:30:13,119 --> 00:30:14,799
Secondly, they are to thank you...

544
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,240
for taking care of me thus far.

545
00:30:17,359 --> 00:30:18,799
Also,

546
00:30:19,079 --> 00:30:23,000
for everything I put you through,

547
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,359
I'm sorry.

548
00:30:27,839 --> 00:30:29,240
I'll make an exception.

549
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,720
Just this once. Don't make it a habit.

550
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,720
Thank you as well.

551
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,359
Two days ago, at the training center,

552
00:30:47,319 --> 00:30:48,720
you worried that I'd be beaten to death,

553
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:49,759
so you tried to protect me.

554
00:30:49,759 --> 00:30:50,759
I could see that.

555
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:54,119
Though it was a bit of a mess,

556
00:30:54,319 --> 00:30:55,359
I'm still quite touched.

557
00:30:55,839 --> 00:30:57,039
You could tell?

558
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:00,480
I'm glad you noticed.

559
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:03,079
I feel bad for you, you know?

560
00:31:03,079 --> 00:31:04,720
It's unfair that you got beaten up.

561
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:05,720
Watching you getting beat up...

562
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:06,799
and knowing how awful you must have felt...

563
00:31:06,799 --> 00:31:07,960
made me even more upset.

564
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,799
So I can't let that happen again.

565
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,079
I'm going to seek justice for you.

566
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,759
Although I'm no match for your instructor,

567
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:17,680
I can make them feel guilty, right?

568
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,359
That's your only option. Here.

569
00:31:21,039 --> 00:31:22,240
There's something...

570
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,400
I didn't want to tell you before.

571
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:26,319
I don't like to talk that much.

572
00:31:27,799 --> 00:31:28,960
But today,

573
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,640
since you agreed to drink with me,

574
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,480
I'll be frank with you...

575
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:34,279
about my impression of you.

576
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,319
I didn't know much about you.

577
00:31:37,759 --> 00:31:39,599
But through our interactions...

578
00:31:39,599 --> 00:31:42,960
and getting to spend more time with you,

579
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,279
I gradually understood.

580
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:46,359
Actually, I feel sorry for you sometimes.

581
00:31:46,359 --> 00:31:47,440
I think...

582
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:50,519
you've come a long way.

583
00:31:50,839 --> 00:31:52,480
I know you grew up...

584
00:31:53,359 --> 00:31:55,079
Your parents got divorced when you were very young.

585
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:57,039
You then joined the cadet school.

586
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:59,440
You trained every day.

587
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:01,480
While others studied, you trained.

588
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,880
While others were shopping, you were training.

589
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:05,559
While others went on dates,

590
00:32:05,559 --> 00:32:06,680
you still trained.

591
00:32:07,279 --> 00:32:08,400
After all these years of training,

592
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:10,400
you got a job...

593
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,359
as well as a boyfriend.

594
00:32:13,599 --> 00:32:15,839
You were in an unreliable relationship.

595
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:17,599
You don't talk about it,

596
00:32:17,599 --> 00:32:19,279
but I know it was a huge blow to you.

597
00:32:19,279 --> 00:32:22,319
From the first time I saw you on the street, chasing him,

598
00:32:23,079 --> 00:32:25,079
to seeing how you reacted...

599
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:28,039
and handled things later,

600
00:32:28,759 --> 00:32:31,279
you might have wrapped yourself up well to protect yourself,

601
00:32:31,279 --> 00:32:32,319
but from the look in your eyes,

602
00:32:32,319 --> 00:32:35,000
from your demeanor,

603
00:32:35,599 --> 00:32:38,119
I saw traces of sadness, sorrow.

604
00:32:38,759 --> 00:32:40,960
Or perhaps...

605
00:32:42,079 --> 00:32:43,839
annoyance towards yourself.

606
00:32:45,799 --> 00:32:47,240
I noticed it.

607
00:32:48,119 --> 00:32:49,359
Sometimes,

608
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,079
I really feel sorry.

609
00:32:51,079 --> 00:32:52,319
Why did you and I...

610
00:32:53,079 --> 00:32:54,240
Although we bicker...

611
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:57,119
and we get into trouble,

612
00:32:57,119 --> 00:32:58,680
but from the bottom of my heart,

613
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,119
I still feel bad for you.

614
00:33:01,319 --> 00:33:02,359
It's because...

615
00:33:02,599 --> 00:33:03,799
I think you deserve to be fussed over.

616
00:33:03,799 --> 00:33:05,359
It's because I believe...

617
00:33:05,599 --> 00:33:06,920
that you will be happy.

618
00:33:07,599 --> 00:33:09,920
Why? It's because you've been through a lot.

619
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:15,039
But I think the earlier ups and downs...

620
00:33:15,039 --> 00:33:17,599
and conflicts are not necessarily a bad thing.

621
00:33:17,599 --> 00:33:20,359
Everything you've been through in your life...

622
00:33:20,359 --> 00:33:22,480
will be your asset for the future.

623
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,559
In the future,

624
00:33:23,559 --> 00:33:25,960
they become your strength.

625
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:28,839
They make you stronger and wiser.

626
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:32,079
But I still...

627
00:33:33,319 --> 00:33:37,079
can't help but feel bad for you.

628
00:33:38,519 --> 00:33:39,680
I feel a little emotional.

629
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:42,440
A girl like you...

630
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,400
Wu Shi Yi, a girl like you...

631
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:46,200
will be happy for sure.

632
00:33:46,519 --> 00:33:48,079
Because if you can't be happy,

633
00:33:48,079 --> 00:33:49,400
no one will.

634
00:33:49,759 --> 00:33:50,839
By the way,

635
00:33:50,839 --> 00:33:52,799
I think you're especially happy to have met me.

636
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:54,160
Don't you think so?

637
00:33:56,039 --> 00:33:58,720
The last sentence is more important, right?

638
00:33:58,720 --> 00:33:59,839
For your happiness.

639
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:01,799
I wish you happiness.

640
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:08,440
Do you feel happy?

641
00:34:11,679 --> 00:34:12,719
Come on.

642
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:14,360
Where are you taking me?

643
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:15,769
It's pitch black.

644
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,559
It's just around the corner. Hurry up.

645
00:34:17,559 --> 00:34:19,679
You're not trying to sell me, are you?

646
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:27,000
This place is like a fairy tale.

647
00:34:27,519 --> 00:34:28,519
Have you been here before?

648
00:34:29,519 --> 00:34:31,329
I remember taking Hou Jue...

649
00:34:31,719 --> 00:34:33,840
to these places when he was a boy.

650
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:34,840
Come on.

651
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,039
- Let's go. - Where to?

652
00:34:37,039 --> 00:34:38,199
Go and play.

653
00:34:38,199 --> 00:34:39,360
I'm not going.

654
00:34:40,039 --> 00:34:41,809
This is for young people.

655
00:34:42,159 --> 00:34:43,559
I can't. Go and have fun.

656
00:34:43,559 --> 00:34:45,289
I'll wait outside. Go.

657
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:48,039
I forgot. You're old.

658
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,719
An old man can't be playing, right?

659
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:52,769
What do you mean?

660
00:34:53,119 --> 00:34:54,360
Are you saying I'm old?

661
00:34:57,289 --> 00:34:59,329
I'll show you.

662
00:34:59,329 --> 00:35:00,400
I'm telling you.

663
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:02,599
Old men won't lose to the youngsters.

664
00:35:03,519 --> 00:35:05,199
Don't be rash.

665
00:35:05,199 --> 00:35:06,719
Recklessness is deadly.

666
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:10,289
That's the exit. The exit.

667
00:35:10,289 --> 00:35:11,960
Over there. The entry is that way.

668
00:35:13,239 --> 00:35:14,329
Do you have money?

669
00:35:14,329 --> 00:35:15,329
Yes.

670
00:35:19,809 --> 00:35:20,880
What is this?

671
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:22,360
You're underestimating me.

672
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:24,289
Listen, if I designed this merry-go-round,

673
00:35:24,289 --> 00:35:26,239
it would be at least double the speed.

674
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,079
According to your design plan,

675
00:35:28,079 --> 00:35:29,880
it would be like a crazy merry-go-round.

676
00:35:31,559 --> 00:35:32,639
You know what?

677
00:35:33,119 --> 00:35:35,480
We didn't have many fun things growing up.

678
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:37,599
We just played...

679
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,400
with little glass beads.

680
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:42,679
That's what we played with.

681
00:35:43,559 --> 00:35:46,769
Or we went to a sandbox and spinning seats.

682
00:35:46,769 --> 00:35:48,000
Spinning seats at the sandbox.

683
00:35:48,239 --> 00:35:49,809
I could play for the whole day.

684
00:35:49,809 --> 00:35:51,840
You young lads are a lucky bunch.

685
00:35:52,519 --> 00:35:55,039
I loved riding on the merry-go-round when I was young.

686
00:35:55,289 --> 00:35:57,360
But I stopped when I entered middle school.

687
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:59,239
At that time, I hung out with my friends.

688
00:35:59,239 --> 00:36:00,519
We would do whatever that was thrilling...

689
00:36:00,519 --> 00:36:02,000
or exciting.

690
00:36:02,199 --> 00:36:03,239
But now,

691
00:36:03,239 --> 00:36:05,199
I still prefer riding the merry-go-round.

692
00:36:05,199 --> 00:36:07,289
I love that it goes slow.

693
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:09,480
Slow?

694
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:12,809
If you said I like to take it slow at my age,

695
00:36:12,809 --> 00:36:13,920
that'd be understandable.

696
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,679
Why do you like to take things slow?

697
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:17,960
What's the saying?

698
00:36:18,599 --> 00:36:19,880
"Walk slowly..."

699
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:21,519
"so the soul can keep up."

700
00:36:21,519 --> 00:36:23,199
I think that's what it means.

701
00:36:24,329 --> 00:36:25,769
It makes sense.

702
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,920
You should age slower as well.

703
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:34,000
I...

704
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,079
Look at me.

705
00:36:36,079 --> 00:36:39,239
I tend to overthink matters.

706
00:36:40,289 --> 00:36:42,289
I tire myself out that way.

707
00:36:42,289 --> 00:36:43,639
I've long forgotten...

708
00:36:43,639 --> 00:36:45,920
how simplicity could be so satisfying.

709
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:46,920
That's right.

710
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:51,329
So according to you,

711
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:53,769
I shouldn't be the doctor to treat your loneliness.

712
00:36:54,159 --> 00:36:56,679
I should be your medicine.

713
00:36:56,679 --> 00:36:58,480
Yes, the cure-all medicine.

714
00:36:59,639 --> 00:37:00,639
Go!

715
00:37:01,039 --> 00:37:02,119
Go!

716
00:37:04,639 --> 00:37:05,719
It's raining.

717
00:37:23,159 --> 00:37:24,159
How is it?

718
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,639
The old man stood up to the challenge, right?

719
00:37:25,639 --> 00:37:26,809
Yes.

720
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,679
Two grilled tripes, please.

721
00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:29,719
All right.

722
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,239
- How much is it? - Ten yuan.

723
00:37:31,239 --> 00:37:32,360
Ten yuan.

724
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:35,329
I should pay for this because you treated my ailment.

725
00:37:36,519 --> 00:37:39,679
Getting treated to a meal is part of the antidote.

726
00:37:39,679 --> 00:37:41,769
I'd be a freeloader.

727
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:43,679
Sir, I've paid the bill.

728
00:37:43,679 --> 00:37:45,000
Bring me two more soft drinks.

729
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,360
- Sure. - How much is it?

730
00:37:46,719 --> 00:37:47,769
Twenty yuan.

731
00:37:49,239 --> 00:37:50,809
- Okay, it's paid. - Okay, thank you.

732
00:37:50,809 --> 00:37:51,840
Here you go.

733
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:52,840
- Thank you. - Thank you.

734
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:53,920
Come on.

735
00:37:55,079 --> 00:37:56,159
Bottoms up.

736
00:37:56,719 --> 00:37:58,239
Wait a minute!

737
00:37:58,239 --> 00:37:59,329
Really?

738
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:02,079
Why are you like this after drinking?

739
00:38:03,329 --> 00:38:04,360
It's true.

740
00:38:08,559 --> 00:38:09,639
Don't drink too much.

741
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:10,920
